>Don't get me wrong, I like a nice wolf as much as the next person but some variety is also nice.
Variety IS nice, but at the same time it all boils down to A) what the readers want to see, and B) what the writer is comfortable writing about. Cats and dogs are popular because they resonate with the audience the most, and I can sort of see why as well. Personally I'd be vaguely interested in a a story about something more exotic like an elephant or an armadillo or a hippo, but honestly only as an "I wonder if someone can pull it off" sort of way. I don't think I'd care to read a really long series with any of those species as the main lead because they just don't hit me the same as cats and dogs.

By all means I welcome some variety, but I don't think we should go "we've enough of ___ already", especially since we're always getting new writers and they should feel comfortable writing what they want to.
